    {
      "id": "section-header-grammar-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Section Header Grammar",
      "position": {
        "x": -80,
        "y": -140
      },
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "width": 560,
      "height": 240,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Section Header Grammar\n\nThis graph defines the first concrete composition law for organizational graphs.\n\nWe are deciding what headers do, what sections are, when clusters exist, and how summary nodes participate without becoming decorative noise.",
